# Implementation Plan — Telemetry Pipeline, HMM State Sequencing & Time-Series Forecasting

This plan outlines the design and implementation of the complete telemetry diagnostic pipeline based on the specifications in [Telemetry Pipeline Plan.pdf](file:///d:/DEVOPS/files/Telemetry%20Pipeline%20Plan.pdf).

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key Pipeline Configurations & Design Decisions:**
> 1. **Data Joining & Alignment**: 
>    - We will merge metrics, logs, and traces on `(episode_id, elapsed_s, timestamp)`. 
>    - Since traces are generated every 4 steps (8 seconds) in the generator, we will aggregate trace-level features per step and forward-fill/fill-zero for steps without trace entries to ensure complete coverage.
> 2. **HMM Parameter Estimation**:
>    - We will define the "true" transition state sequence for the training episodes based on the transition timeline (healthy in the first 80s, failure state in the middle, and crash/recovery in the end).
>    - We will estimate the Transition Matrix $A$ and Emission Matrix $B$ (representing classifier confusion) directly from the training set, then run the Viterbi algorithm natively to find the most probable hidden state sequence for each test episode.
> 3. **Tumbling Mode**:
>    - We will tumble the step-level predictions into 60-second windows (30 steps each) using the mode of each window. For 240-second episodes, this will produce 4 windows (`t1` to `t4`). To match the template's 5-row layout, we will also output a 48s-window version (5 windows of 24 steps each) as `HMM_Test_Data_State_Sequence_With_Tumbling_Mode_5win.xlsx` to prevent any structural divergence.
> 4. **ARIMA Metric Forecasting**:
>    - We will fit ARIMA models on 9 key metrics: CPU Utilization, Memory Utilization, P50 Latency, P95 Latency, P99 Latency, Error Rate, Request Rate, Cache Hit Rate, and Queue Lag.
>    - The models will be trained on the first 90 steps (180 seconds) and forecast the remaining 30 steps (60 seconds) to evaluate MAE, RMSE, and MAPE.

> [!WARNING]
> **Package Installations Needed:**
> - `statsmodels` (for ARIMA forecasting)
> - `openpyxl` (for Excel read/write)

